title: Awful
text: Iâ€™ve suffered from and recovered from an eating disorder, and for the past few years, itâ€™s been very dormant and insignificant - however, for some reason, Twitter (X) continues recommending me pro-anorexia content. I thought it was a weird coincidence at first (even though I have NEVER interacted with eating disorder content on X and click â€œdonâ€™t recommend similar postsâ€ every time I see a similar post) but itâ€™s been MONTHS and it still happens. Multiple people (100+) have told me they experience the same thing. I have no idea what the reason is for this boosting of destructive eating disorder content, but it has made me entirely leave the app so I can avoid risking a relapse. Iâ€™ve been upset with the boosting of right-wing content, but I can accept different opinions than me â€” what I CANâ€™T accept is the promotion of self-destructive mental illnesses that happens on the app. There is something seriously and nefariously wrong with the algorithm that I believe is doing substantial harm to society. I give it two stars instead of one because I still see some tweets that arenâ€™t awful and the bar is very low.
